The paper investigates the quality of features produced by deep neural network architectures obtained by stacking and convolving Auto-Encoders for a classification task. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the training error and the results obtained if the same features were used for both input reconstruction and a classification task, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses document layout analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
